            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think the underlying issue is that 'splitkeep' handles screen states that were not seen by the user, similar to #23888. I had a back and forth with Bram about this in https://github.com/vim/vim/pull/12488, there is no solution yet. \r\n\r\nI think it would make sense to let vim just update the topline when necessary if the cursor position was updated in between one redraw to the next, although it is a bit unpredictable. But 'splitkeep' \"stabilizing\" the next screen state only makes if the previous screen state(read cursor position) was actually seen by the user in the first place.",
